transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra. Quinn speaking. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, my name is Steve Lemay. I just received an order from Score Blue. I didn't order it.

Speaker 1: I got one. It didn't work. I thought I canceled.

Speaker 2: I can take a look and see what's going on.

Speaker 1: I want to cancel.

Speaker 2: Yeah, okay. Well, if it's not working, sir, you know, we can always send you some more for free

Speaker 1: and see if that's working for you better, too.

Speaker 2: You don't have to cancel automatically at all, sir. You can choose when you get your orders.

Speaker 1: It's up to you. You don't have to get them when you're not ready.

Speaker 2: I just want to return what I got or do I have to get these?

Speaker 1: That's up to you, sir, but, I mean, if they're not working,

Speaker 2: why would you not want to try something else for free?

Speaker 1: Well, I want to give you these back. I haven't opened them.

Speaker 2: I mean, I took them out of the package, but I didn't open them.

Speaker 1: I was asking about sending you something for free, though.

Speaker 2: I do understand you have those and they're not working.

Speaker 1: We're on the same page.

Speaker 2: I'm trying to send you some more for free to see if they work for you.

Speaker 1: We're not going to bill you or send you anything else until we find something to work for you.

Speaker 2: What's a different one?

Speaker 1: This would be a different manufacturer.

Speaker 2: This is going to be our AGV that comes from France,

Speaker 1: not the one that was in America, the one that you received.

Speaker 2: I'm not sure if you're aware how Viagra works.

Speaker 1: It's a vasomedication, which is about moving blood flow through your body,

Speaker 2: which ultimately gives you an erection.

Speaker 1: I understand all that.

Speaker 2: It's very, very subject to body chemistry.

Speaker 1: So certain pills, this pill, just seems like it's not a good fit for you.

Speaker 2: That's why we do offer, we'll send you another one for free.

Speaker 1: It's usually the case. This will be a better fit for you.

Speaker 2: It's a different manufacturer.

Speaker 1: Usually it is the case that you're trying to find something that fits best for your body,

Speaker 2: which is why, like I said, we won't send you this one anymore.

Speaker 1: We'll stop the billing, and we'll send you this one more for free of the newest stuff we have.

Speaker 2: All we do is ask that you give me a phone call.

Speaker 1: I'll give you my extension and let me know if it's working for you.

Speaker 2: When it is, you can let me know when you'd like to receive it or order as needed, whatever you'd like.

Speaker 1: Okay, if I've already got one shipment, this is a second shipment.

Speaker 2: I want to return the second shipment unopened.

Speaker 1: Is that possible?

Speaker 2: That's fine. That is totally fine.

Speaker 1: Do you want to try this new stuff or not?

Speaker 2: I'll try it one time, yeah, the new stuff.

Speaker 1: But I'll still send you this back for credit.

Speaker 2: Well, if it works, I mean, if I send you the new stuff and it actually works, which more than likely it will,

Speaker 1: I could just simply replace it with the stuff that works for you so you don't have to worry about shipping that back.

Speaker 2: We'll use the same value that you paid, and I'll send you more bills.

Speaker 1: There's no reason keeping this bottle because it doesn't work.

Speaker 2: I mean, I've gone through the first bottle.

Speaker 1: Just listen to me, sir. Just listen.

Speaker 2: That's why I said that when I send you the new pills, if the new pills work for you,

Speaker 1: then I would simply just tell you I'll throw those away,

Speaker 2: and we will replace the money that you spent with the stuff that works for you.

Speaker 1: So we're not going to reship you the stuff that's not working.

Speaker 2: We're going to send you more of the pills that are working for you,

Speaker 1: and that way you don't have to worry about shipping those back and dealing with all that.

Speaker 2: I mean, you're more than willing to. You can.

Speaker 1: But I'm just letting you know that it is okay.

Speaker 2: We don't mind exchanging and swapping those out for the ones that actually work for you.

Speaker 1: Or you can just send them back, sir. We'll give you your money. It's up to you.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I'll send them back.

Speaker 1: All right, just send them back.

Speaker 2: Do I need an RF, a return authorization number?

Speaker 1: No, no, no. I don't need any of that, sir.

Speaker 2: We don't send any kind of return slips or anything like that either.

Speaker 1: I've got an address of shipping manager 525 Alexandria Pike, Southgate, Kentucky.

Speaker 2: Correct.

Speaker 1: Do I return it to there?

Speaker 2: Correct.

Speaker 1: Is that what I send it back to?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: That will do. I appreciate the help.

Speaker 1: You're welcome.

Speaker 2: You have a good day.
